SIMPLE: overtop
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overtop
<hw>O`ver*top"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overtopped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overtopping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To rise
above the top of; to exceed in height; to tower above.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To
<xex>o'ertop</xex> old Pelion.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To go beyond; to transcend; to transgress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If kings presume to <qex>overtop</qex> the law by which they
reign, . . . they are by law to be reduced into order.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To make of less importance, or throw into the
background, by superior excellence; to dwarf; to obscure.</def>
<rj><au>Becon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overtower</ent>⟦br⟧
